‐ [roaring]

6
00:00:30,982 --> 00:00:37,989
<i>♪ ♪</i>

7
00:00:51,252 --> 00:00:53,421
‐ The whole Iron Tribe

8
00:00:53,421 --> 00:00:55,924
shall be exterminated.

9
00:00:55,924 --> 00:01:02,972
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10
00:01:05,266 --> 00:01:06,267
‐ Open fire!

11
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:13,316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12
00:01:23,159 --> 00:01:26,997
[whooshing]

13
00:01:26,997 --> 00:01:29,457
‐ [roaring]

14
00:01:29,457 --> 00:01:36,381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15
00:01:36,381 --> 00:01:39,384
["Gravitation" by Angela]

16
00:01:39,384 --> 00:01:42,470
[woman singing in Japanese]

17
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:49,477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18
00:03:14,896 --> 00:03:19,067
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19
00:03:19,067 --> 00:03:20,902
[explosion booms]

20
00:03:20,902 --> 00:03:27,951
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21
00:03:31,871 --> 00:03:34,916
<i>[dramatic choral music]</i>

22
00:03:34,916 --> 00:03:41,923
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23
00:03:41,923 --> 00:03:43,383
[boom]

24
00:03:51,766 --> 00:03:52,767
[blasters firing]

25
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:59,816
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26
00:04:00,859 --> 00:04:01,943
[boom]

27
00:04:01,943 --> 00:04:08,950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28
00:04:19,419 --> 00:04:21,129
WOMAN: [gasps]

29
00:04:21,129 --> 00:04:22,839
[nervous chatter]

30
00:04:22,839 --> 00:04:25,842
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31
00:04:25,842 --> 00:04:27,302
‐ [groans]

32
00:04:27,302 --> 00:04:29,012
Pull out!
Get out of here!

33
00:04:29,012 --> 00:04:30,847
There's just too many of them!

34
00:04:30,847 --> 00:04:34,017
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35
00:04:34,017 --> 00:04:36,811
‐ [roaring]

36
00:04:36,811 --> 00:04:43,860
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37
00:04:56,706 --> 00:05:00,668
[shimmering tone]

38
00:05:00,668 --> 00:05:02,253
[roaring]

39
00:05:04,339 --> 00:05:05,840
[roaring]

40
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:10,220
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:13,681
[rumbling]

42
00:05:13,681 --> 00:05:15,683
[nervous chatter]

43
00:05:15,683 --> 00:05:17,018
‐ Retreat!

44
00:05:17,018 --> 00:05:19,729
That Nodos is going
to kill us all!

45
00:05:19,729 --> 00:05:24,192
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46
00:05:24,192 --> 00:05:27,070
‐ They're so quick to abandon
the one who protects them.

47
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:30,490
It appears they are nothing
more than a race of cowards.

48
00:05:30,490 --> 00:05:32,909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49
00:05:32,909 --> 00:05:34,452
MAN: Second engine down!
MAN: Spread out!

50
00:05:34,452 --> 00:05:35,870
MAN: Second engine down!

51
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:37,622
This isn't good!
There's too many!

52
00:05:37,622 --> 00:05:40,583
I can't shake them!
[screaming]

53
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:43,836
‐ All fleets on the front line
are to begin tactical retreat.

54
00:05:43,836 --> 00:05:46,839
Fleets in the rear are
to provide covering fire.

55
00:05:46,839 --> 00:05:48,883
Now, access strategic data.

56
00:05:48,883 --> 00:05:51,761
We need to prioritize
counterattack protocols.

57
00:05:51,761 --> 00:05:53,846
‐ Yes, ma'am.
‐ Where is Bellcross now?

58
00:05:53,846 --> 00:05:55,390
‐ He's currently engaging
the bulk

59
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:57,141
of the Bronze Tribe's forces
in orbit.

60
00:05:57,141 --> 00:05:59,560
‐ If only there were some way
for us to communicate

61
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:02,313
our strategy to him.

62
00:06:02,313 --> 00:06:05,483
‐ [roaring]

63
00:06:05,483 --> 00:06:06,567
[rumbling]

64
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:09,279
<i>♪ ♪</i>

65
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,738
[roaring]

66
00:06:13,116 --> 00:06:16,035
[roaring]

67
00:06:16,035 --> 00:06:22,083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

68
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:25,086
MAHITAK: When I helped out
Karkinos,

69
00:06:25,086 --> 00:06:28,256
the fifth one didn't try
to hurt him anymore.

70
00:06:28,256 --> 00:06:33,428
Maybe the other Nodos doesn't
want to destroy anything either.

71
00:06:33,428 --> 00:06:37,098
‐ Yet he fights so savagely on
the forefront of the Iron Tribe.

72
00:06:37,098 --> 00:06:41,102
Unable to find aid even from his
own people.

73
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:44,897
‐ All by himself?

74
00:06:44,897 --> 00:06:46,649
By why would he?

75
00:06:46,649 --> 00:06:51,487
‐ That is most certainly a Labor
that was demanded of him.

76
00:06:51,487 --> 00:06:53,322
‐ I despise them.

77
00:06:53,322 --> 00:06:55,408
I wish there were no Labors.

78
00:06:58,369 --> 00:07:01,914
[soft rumbling]

79
00:07:07,295 --> 00:07:08,504
DHIANEILA: Age.

80
00:07:10,423 --> 00:07:12,884
[whooshing]

81
00:07:12,884 --> 00:07:13,926
[deep rumbling]

82
00:07:21,517 --> 00:07:24,979
[electricity zapping]

83
00:07:24,979 --> 00:07:26,189
MELEAGROS: What are you doing?

84
00:07:26,189 --> 00:07:27,982
Send in everything we've got!

85
00:07:27,982 --> 00:07:31,319
It is absolutely unacceptable
to keep humiliating ourselves

86
00:07:31,319 --> 00:07:33,071
in front of our ancient god.

87
00:07:33,071 --> 00:07:35,615
‐ We have to focus on
a strategic counterattack.

88
00:07:35,615 --> 00:07:38,076
We might actually have a chance
if we can draw them

89
00:07:38,076 --> 00:07:41,245
a quarter of a cycle from their
current orbital position.

90
00:07:41,245 --> 00:07:44,165
‐ Are you suggesting that we run
from them?

91
00:07:44,165 --> 00:07:48,002
ATALANTES: I would use the main
cannon, if I were you.

92
00:07:48,002 --> 00:07:49,629
‐ The main cannon.

93
00:07:49,629 --> 00:07:52,173
‐ It would certainly destroy
the Bronze Tribe's hide.

94
00:07:52,173 --> 00:07:54,217
Of course that much
planetary debris

95
00:07:54,217 --> 00:07:56,677
would ignite Jupiter's core.

96
00:07:56,677 --> 00:07:58,554
NILVAL: What did you just say?

97
00:07:58,554 --> 00:08:00,556
ATALANTES:
An explosion of that order

98
00:08:00,556 --> 00:08:04,018
would seriously weaken
the Silver Tribe's fleet.

99
00:08:04,018 --> 00:08:07,396
‐ Yes, but wouldn't that weaken
our fleet as well?

100
00:08:07,396 --> 00:08:09,732
‐ A few casualties in battle
are inevitable.

101
00:08:09,732 --> 00:08:12,527
‐ You can't honestly be ordering
us to destroy a planet

102
00:08:12,527 --> 00:08:14,529
in our own solar system.

103
00:08:14,529 --> 00:08:17,323
‐ I like it.
Prepare to fire the main cannon!

104
00:08:17,323 --> 00:08:18,699
‐ No, don't do it!

105
00:08:18,699 --> 00:08:20,451
‐ Believe me, I take absolutely
no pleasure

106
00:08:20,451 --> 00:08:23,079
in sacrificing the holy planet
of Jupiter.

107
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:26,541
But it's critical that we never
show our back to the enemy.

108
00:08:26,541 --> 00:08:29,460
NILVAL: And Nodos is fighting
in the blast radius.

109
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:32,755
‐ Oh, I seriously doubt that
we'll harm our precious Nodos.

110
00:08:32,755 --> 00:08:35,133
‐ And how do you know that?

111
00:08:35,133 --> 00:08:37,760
‐ Prepare the cannon to fire.

112
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,303
‐ Target the planet Io.

113
00:08:39,303 --> 00:08:40,638
Deliver orders for all fleets

114
00:08:40,638 --> 00:08:42,682
to move out of orbit
immediately!

115
00:08:42,682 --> 00:08:45,059
NILVAL: [scoffs]
Disregard that!

116
00:08:45,059 --> 00:08:46,727
Do not fire, no matter what!

117
00:08:46,727 --> 00:08:48,896
‐ Who do you think you are?

118
00:08:48,896 --> 00:08:50,440
ATALANTES: [clears throat]

119
00:08:52,358 --> 00:08:56,112
Explain yourself, Nilval.

120
00:08:56,112 --> 00:08:57,947
‐ There are consequences.

121
00:08:57,947 --> 00:08:59,532
You aren't just destroying
a planet;

122
00:08:59,532 --> 00:09:01,200
you're damaging allies too.

123
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,910
The soldiers will be demoralized

124
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:04,954
and allegiances
will be strained.

125
00:09:04,954 --> 00:09:07,540
‐ Hmm.
Well, in that case‐‐

126
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:09,125
‐ Big brother!

127
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:11,210
‐ It seems the lieutenant
general has lost her nerve.

128
00:09:11,210 --> 00:09:12,920
How pathetic.

129
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:15,506
It's obvious to me she can
no longer handle the pressure

130
00:09:15,506 --> 00:09:16,507
of her position.

131
00:09:16,507 --> 00:09:18,009
‐ [groans]

132
00:09:18,009 --> 00:09:19,510
‐ She's no longer fit for duty

133
00:09:19,510 --> 00:09:21,387
and shall be removed
from her post.

134
00:09:21,387 --> 00:09:22,763
I should have you arrested,

135
00:09:22,763 --> 00:09:25,475
but you're popular with
the troops.

136
00:09:25,475 --> 00:09:28,019
Be thankful for that.

137
00:09:28,019 --> 00:09:29,937
‐ You bastards.

138
00:09:29,937 --> 00:09:31,063
<i>[tense music]</i>

139
00:09:31,063 --> 00:09:32,607
MAN: Now deploying barrels.

140
00:09:32,607 --> 00:09:35,443
Activating all gravity
anti‐particle accelerators.

141
00:09:35,443 --> 00:09:37,445
No errors detected.

142
00:09:37,445 --> 00:09:39,739
MAN: Charging gravitational
prism.

143
00:09:39,739 --> 00:09:41,949
Normal energy conduction
confirmed.

144
00:09:41,949 --> 00:09:48,956
<i>♪ ♪</i>

145
00:09:58,299 --> 00:10:00,551
‐ It's exactly like
the princess said:

146
00:10:00,551 --> 00:10:03,596
This is a meaningless exercise
in destruction.

147
00:10:03,596 --> 00:10:05,431
‐ I suppose it can't be helped.

148
00:10:05,431 --> 00:10:08,851
This fight will affect both
Mars and Jupiter.

149
00:10:08,851 --> 00:10:10,520
‐ Tell me the truth.

150
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:14,148
How much of our fleet can
survive something like this?

151
00:10:14,148 --> 00:10:17,818
‐ We have no other choice but
to hope that Age will save us.

152
00:10:17,818 --> 00:10:19,529
‐ He's fighting to protect us,

153
00:10:19,529 --> 00:10:22,240
but we're powerless to return
the favor.

154
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,282
‐ [sighs]

155
00:10:25,201 --> 00:10:26,994
‐ [whimpers softly]

156
00:10:26,994 --> 00:10:29,330
‐ What's the matter?

157
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:32,375
‐ Something terrible.
‐ What are you talking about?

158
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:33,584
‐ [moans]

159
00:10:33,584 --> 00:10:34,794
Something is happening,

160
00:10:34,794 --> 00:10:37,004
and it can never be undone.

161
00:10:37,004 --> 00:10:39,507
It's so awful.

162
00:10:39,507 --> 00:10:41,342
It starts now.

163
00:10:41,342 --> 00:10:42,385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

164
00:10:42,385 --> 00:10:43,803
MAN: Accelerator, good to go.

165
00:10:43,803 --> 00:10:45,179
MAN: All systems optimal.

166
00:10:45,179 --> 00:10:46,430
Barrels are in place.

167
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:48,683
MAN: Activating
echo location device.

168
00:10:48,683 --> 00:10:51,269
[inaudible] cartridge,
locked and loaded.

169
00:10:51,269 --> 00:10:52,853
[zapping]

170
00:10:52,853 --> 00:10:59,026
<i>♪ ♪</i>

171
00:10:59,026 --> 00:11:01,279
‐ When this star dies...

172
00:11:03,239 --> 00:11:04,699
[gasps]

173
00:11:04,699 --> 00:11:08,035
<i>♪ ♪</i>

174
00:11:08,035 --> 00:11:09,245
‐ It's been confirmed.

175
00:11:09,245 --> 00:11:12,123
The main cannon
is ready to fire.

176
00:11:12,123 --> 00:11:14,500
‐ [chuckles] Perfect.

177
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,002
Well, brother?

178
00:11:16,002 --> 00:11:18,379
‐ [chuckles] Destroy them.

179
00:11:18,379 --> 00:11:20,423
[zapping]

180
00:11:23,342 --> 00:11:27,179
[wind blowing softly]

181
00:11:27,179 --> 00:11:29,181
[zapping]

182
00:11:31,934 --> 00:11:34,103
[rumbling]

183
00:11:34,103 --> 00:11:36,897
[beeping]

184
00:11:36,897 --> 00:11:39,650
MAN: Sir, Io is falling
from orbit.

185
00:11:39,650 --> 00:11:40,651
‐ Hmm.

186
00:11:42,737 --> 00:11:44,155
MAN: Alert fleet.

187
00:11:44,155 --> 00:11:45,906
The Bronze Tribe
is abandoning the planet.

188
00:11:45,906 --> 00:11:47,908
‐ Hmm.

189
00:11:47,908 --> 00:11:49,952
[soft rumbling]

190
00:12:00,588 --> 00:12:02,632
[deep rumbling]

191
00:12:09,430 --> 00:12:12,683
‐ They would do that
to their own planet?

192
00:12:12,683 --> 00:12:14,518
That must be the reason
the Silver Tribe

193
00:12:14,518 --> 00:12:17,271
wishes to destroy
the entire species.

194
00:12:21,275 --> 00:12:23,319
[wind blowing]

195
00:12:30,951 --> 00:12:31,869
[whoosh]

196
00:12:31,869 --> 00:12:34,955
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

197
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:41,962
<i>♪ ♪</i>

198
00:12:44,298 --> 00:12:45,633
‐ Now deploy.

199
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:52,640
<i>♪ ♪</i>

200
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:04,360
‐ Princess Dhianeila.

201
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,403
ALL: Your majesty!

202
00:13:05,403 --> 00:13:07,822
DHIANEILA: [whimpers]

203
00:13:07,822 --> 00:13:10,282
I don't know what's happening.

204
00:13:10,282 --> 00:13:13,202
Where is he?
Where is age?

205
00:13:13,202 --> 00:13:16,247
[rumbling]

206
00:13:22,253 --> 00:13:24,922
ATALANTES: [laughing]

207
00:13:24,922 --> 00:13:27,049
Look at them scattering
like insects.

208
00:13:27,049 --> 00:13:29,719
A most excellent strategy,
Atalantes.

209
00:13:29,719 --> 00:13:31,846
‐ Why, thank you, big brother.

210
00:13:31,846 --> 00:13:33,681
‐ Sir, we can't locate
the Nodos.

211
00:13:33,681 --> 00:13:36,517
It looks like he may have been
caught in the explosion.

212
00:13:36,517 --> 00:13:37,977
‐ Find it now.

213
00:13:37,977 --> 00:13:39,854
The infernal goliath
still has a lot of work to do

214
00:13:39,854 --> 00:13:41,856
for us around here.

215
00:13:41,856 --> 00:13:43,899
‐ Don't let this chance slip by.

216
00:13:43,899 --> 00:13:47,653
Straighten the line
and charge the enemy!

217
00:13:47,653 --> 00:13:49,280
‐ They ordered
an offensive charge

218
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:51,866
right after the fleet
got torn apart.

219
00:13:51,866 --> 00:13:53,826
Those two imbeciles.

220
00:13:53,826 --> 00:13:55,703
As long as we can keep
the enemy engaged,

221
00:13:55,703 --> 00:13:58,747
I want to maintain a comm link
with the "Argonaut."

222
00:13:58,747 --> 00:14:00,082
[rapid beeping]

223
00:14:00,082 --> 00:14:01,083
[gasps]

224
00:14:03,502 --> 00:14:10,509
<i>♪ ♪</i>

225
00:14:22,897 --> 00:14:24,732
‐ Now drive it back.

226
00:14:24,732 --> 00:14:31,780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

227
00:14:35,618 --> 00:14:36,785
‐ What?

228
00:14:36,785 --> 00:14:43,834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

229
00:14:48,631 --> 00:14:49,673
[music stops]

230
00:14:55,429 --> 00:14:58,807
[muffled booming]

231
00:14:58,807 --> 00:15:00,851
[zapping]

232
00:15:13,614 --> 00:15:14,740
‐ Oh, no.

233
00:15:14,740 --> 00:15:16,825
I don't believe what I'm seeing!

234
00:15:16,825 --> 00:15:18,118
We're in trouble!

235
00:15:18,118 --> 00:15:19,578
‐ [gasps]

236
00:15:19,578 --> 00:15:22,289
The Silver Tribe wasn't supposed
to interfere.

237
00:15:22,289 --> 00:15:24,375
And wasn't in the database.

238
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:27,670
‐ Soon enough we'll have
a full‐scale panic on our hands.

239
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:29,213
That'll be
the perfect opportunity

240
00:15:29,213 --> 00:15:30,923
to seize control of the fleet

241
00:15:30,923 --> 00:15:33,842
and order the surviving vessels
to withdraw from the area.

242
00:15:33,842 --> 00:15:34,843
Got it?

243
00:15:37,096 --> 00:15:40,349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

244
00:15:40,349 --> 00:15:43,435
[cracking and rumbling]

245
00:15:43,435 --> 00:15:46,230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

246
00:15:46,230 --> 00:15:48,440
‐ Damn their whole species.

247
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:55,447
<i>♪ ♪</i>

248
00:16:07,501 --> 00:16:10,838
‐ Well, Bellcross,
you've made your decision.

249
00:16:10,838 --> 00:16:12,881
And you shall die with
the foolish ones.

250
00:16:12,881 --> 00:16:14,883
<i>♪ ♪</i>

251
00:16:14,883 --> 00:16:16,927
[rumbling]

252
00:16:18,887 --> 00:16:22,057
<i>♪ ♪</i>

253
00:16:22,057 --> 00:16:23,892
[whoosh]

254
00:16:23,892 --> 00:16:28,522
<i>♪ ♪</i>

255
00:16:28,522 --> 00:16:30,482
‐ Karkinos, get him.

256
00:16:30,482 --> 00:16:36,030
<i>♪ ♪</i>

257
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:37,364
[boom]

258
00:16:37,364 --> 00:16:39,533
‐ It seems Karkinos has begun
the battle.

259
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:42,703
Soon I shall enter it with him.

260
00:16:42,703 --> 00:16:44,955
‐ Let me go instead.

261
00:16:44,955 --> 00:16:47,166
I don't want you to get hurt.

262
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:49,793
Allow me to go in your place,
Lecty.

263
00:16:49,793 --> 00:16:52,296
Please.

264
00:16:52,296 --> 00:16:55,716
‐ I must go.
I promise I'll be fine.

265
00:16:55,716 --> 00:16:56,967
Thank you.

266
00:16:56,967 --> 00:16:57,968
‐ Oh.

267
00:17:08,562 --> 00:17:11,607
[indistinct chatter]

268
00:17:14,276 --> 00:17:17,029
‐ You're looking at
the latest info from Nilval.

269
00:17:17,029 --> 00:17:20,115
It's painfully clear this
is the result of executing

270
00:17:20,115 --> 00:17:21,408
Meleagros' strategy.

271
00:17:21,408 --> 00:17:23,243
IOLAOUS: Those idiots!

272
00:17:23,243 --> 00:17:24,912
They destroyed it!

273
00:17:24,912 --> 00:17:26,413
The entire planet!

274
00:17:26,413 --> 00:17:28,123
DHIANEILA:
What have they done?

275
00:17:28,123 --> 00:17:30,376
‐ [gasps]

276
00:17:30,376 --> 00:17:33,379
IOLAOUS: Princess Dhianeila,
your condition.

277
00:17:33,379 --> 00:17:34,380
[gasps]

278
00:17:38,759 --> 00:17:42,388
‐ Your highness,
why have you come?

279
00:17:42,388 --> 00:17:44,264
‐ I need to know what happened,

280
00:17:44,264 --> 00:17:46,517
to make sense of it all.

281
00:17:46,517 --> 00:17:49,103
I knew that you and Nilval had
been secretly communicating

282
00:17:49,103 --> 00:17:52,189
and now I know why you would do
such a thing:

283
00:17:52,189 --> 00:17:53,941
to stop them.

284
00:17:53,941 --> 00:17:55,985
[beeping]

285
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:01,031
Why would they do this?

286
00:18:01,031 --> 00:18:02,950
Something so horrific?

287
00:18:02,950 --> 00:18:05,828
Those fools.

288
00:18:05,828 --> 00:18:09,289
[crying]

289
00:18:09,289 --> 00:18:11,500
‐ The alliance sustained
significant damage

290
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:13,460
during the operation,

291
00:18:13,460 --> 00:18:17,047
and we still have not been able
to locate the Nodos.

292
00:18:17,047 --> 00:18:20,759
We must begin rescue and repair
procedures immediately.

293
00:18:20,759 --> 00:18:24,138
Then reorganize the fleet.

294
00:18:24,138 --> 00:18:25,431
I apologize.

295
00:18:25,431 --> 00:18:27,933
I realize that this is
the last thing

296
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:29,476
you want to hear right now,

297
00:18:29,476 --> 00:18:31,979
but everyone who reports
to Lieutenant General Nilval

298
00:18:31,979 --> 00:18:33,981
as well as 17 other fleets

299
00:18:33,981 --> 00:18:37,317
have quietly agreed to stay
in the alliance,

300
00:18:37,317 --> 00:18:40,738
after you assume command.

301
00:18:40,738 --> 00:18:41,739
Ah‐‐

302
00:18:42,823 --> 00:18:44,700
‐ You do realize
you're asking me

303
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:49,204
to lead a coup d'etat
against my own brothers.

304
00:18:49,204 --> 00:18:50,748
No.

305
00:18:50,748 --> 00:18:54,001
Now is not the time to instigate
political upheaval.

306
00:18:56,962 --> 00:18:59,465
Instead we need to focus on
wounded soldiers

307
00:18:59,465 --> 00:19:00,841
and damaged vessels.

308
00:19:00,841 --> 00:19:03,343
We shall take them all in
at any cost.

309
00:19:03,343 --> 00:19:06,889
Our primary objective is to save
as many lives as possible.

310
00:19:06,889 --> 00:19:09,600
‐ Then the first step
is moving all rear units

311
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,227
to the terminal planet to set up
the infrastructure

312
00:19:12,227 --> 00:19:14,229
for a massive rescue operation.

313
00:19:14,229 --> 00:19:15,606
‐ I will be coming with you.

314
00:19:15,606 --> 00:19:17,691
Make preparations for
the "Argonaut"

315
00:19:17,691 --> 00:19:19,026
to move out immediately.

316
00:19:19,026 --> 00:19:20,152
MOBEEDO: Yes, ma'am.

317
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,535
MAN: Route formation complete.

318
00:19:28,535 --> 00:19:30,621
Locking in destination.

319
00:19:30,621 --> 00:19:33,207
WOMAN: Setting warp path
to [inaudible].

320
00:19:33,207 --> 00:19:34,833
MAN: Begin warp process.

321
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:37,294
‐ To think Princess Dhianeila
just walked into a room

322
00:19:37,294 --> 00:19:39,421
full of people,
when she's so terrified

323
00:19:39,421 --> 00:19:43,342
of touching another's
consciousness.

324
00:19:43,342 --> 00:19:46,929
She didn't reject the plan,
just the timing.

325
00:19:48,388 --> 00:19:51,683
Your awakening of our star
is near, Nilval.

326
00:19:56,021 --> 00:20:00,109
‐ Are you still out there
fighting all by yourself?

327
00:20:00,109 --> 00:20:05,072
Even after the ones you're
protecting abandoned you.

328
00:20:05,072 --> 00:20:06,657
Just don't die.

329
00:20:08,075 --> 00:20:11,245
‐ I can strongly sense
Age's presence.

330
00:20:11,245 --> 00:20:12,579
We should have gone with him,

331
00:20:12,579 --> 00:20:14,414
instead of staying safely behind

332
00:20:14,414 --> 00:20:17,251
and letting him battle
our enemies all by himself.

333
00:20:17,251 --> 00:20:20,129
Do you think I'm arrogant
for feeling this way?

334
00:20:22,422 --> 00:20:27,427
When Age left, I didn't even
make an effort to keep him here.

335
00:20:27,427 --> 00:20:29,346
The man who fights alone.

336
00:20:31,723 --> 00:20:33,433
‐ If you want my opinion,

337
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:36,645
I think he chose to do all
of this for you, Princess.

338
00:20:36,645 --> 00:20:37,813
‐ What?

339
00:20:39,648 --> 00:20:42,734
‐ May I speak frankly,
your highness?

340
00:20:42,734 --> 00:20:43,777
‐ Yes.

341
00:20:43,777 --> 00:20:45,404
‐ Would you please
stop pretending

342
00:20:45,404 --> 00:20:47,614
you aren't the true leader
of humankind?

343
00:20:47,614 --> 00:20:49,575
Because of our
unwavering faith in you,

344
00:20:49,575 --> 00:20:52,828
all of mankind will gladly walk
the path you choose for us,

345
00:20:52,828 --> 00:20:53,912
your highness.

346
00:20:56,832 --> 00:20:59,334
‐ [sobbing]

347
00:20:59,334 --> 00:21:03,005
Thank you, Aneasha.

348
00:21:03,005 --> 00:21:04,131
WOMAN: All sails down.

349
00:21:04,131 --> 00:21:06,633
Activate dimensional route.

350
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:08,468
‐ Now commencing rescue
operations

351
00:21:08,468 --> 00:21:10,304
for the alliance fleet.

352
00:21:10,304 --> 00:21:12,389
All ships begin warp now.

353
00:21:12,389 --> 00:21:14,600
[rumbling]

354
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,018
[crackling]

355
00:21:16,018 --> 00:21:18,061
[shimmering]

356
00:21:24,318 --> 00:21:27,321
<i>[tense music]</i>

357
00:21:27,321 --> 00:21:34,369
<i>♪ ♪</i>

358
00:21:35,996 --> 00:21:37,581
LECTY: Any measure of brute
strength

359
00:21:37,581 --> 00:21:42,252
is utterly inconsequential
to the flow of time.

360
00:21:42,252 --> 00:21:46,840
Nothing can stand up to
the power of my Erymanthos.

361
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:50,344
<i>♪ ♪</i>

362
00:21:50,344 --> 00:21:51,511
Right there.

363
00:21:51,511 --> 00:21:54,306
We're going to jump Erymanthos.

364
00:21:54,306 --> 00:21:55,891
[shimmering]

365
00:21:58,769 --> 00:22:01,313
Go back to 70 seconds ago.

366
00:22:01,313 --> 00:22:03,523
[whoosh]

367
00:22:03,523 --> 00:22:10,572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

368
